<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="219" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,768,937]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,804,829]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Genital fork medial tubercle absent; apex of arm sharply incurved apically and inflated, fist-like, with long, dense setulae. Distiphallus slightly shorter than phallapodeme, terminating in curved filaments, not inflated apically. Pregonite lobed apically. Postgonite with 
<number box="[811,825,877,901]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="1.0">1</number>
apical seta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
